<dl id="n08049i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08049i">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08049i"> 49(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> canaille never sentenced / lives on loans / &amp; is 35 <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n08049i"><li>FW 173.07 </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/lexg.htm#n08049i">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/g/l39g.htm#n08049i">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n08049i">MS BL 47471b-51</ms> </li><li>JJA 47:333 <a name="g10d" href="../../FF/fdra/gda.htm#g10d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/g/g10d.htm#n08049i">Draft: I.7&sect;1.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">L&apos;auteur de la fig. 166, alt&egrave;re la v&eacute;rit&eacute; par faiblesse, par vanit&eacute;, par paresse.Il a l&apos;ecriture tordue des d&eacute;biles, le trac&eacute; petit et filiforme des d&eacute;prim&eacute;s, les <i>t</i> non barr&eacute;s des n&eacute;gligents, les <i>d</i> enroul&eacute;s des gens satisfaits d&apos;eux-m&ecirc;mes, les <i>o</i> bien ferm&eacute;s et boucl&eacute;s des imp&eacute;n&eacute;trables, et il met des majuscules &agrave; la place des minuscules comme les gens exalt&eacute;s, d&eacute;pourvus de jugement. C&apos;est une canaille. Il n&apos;a jamis subi la plus petite condemnation, mais ses tares profondes l&apos;ont pr&eacute;cipit&eacute; avec sa famille dans une mis&egrave;re noire. Il vit d&apos;emprunt, de mendicit&eacute;, et il a trente-cinq ans. <br><font color="green">[The author of fig. 166 alters truth through weakness, vanity, laziness. He has the twisted writing of the imbecile, the small filigree strokes of the depressed, the uncrossed <i>t</i>&apos;s of the negligent, the coiled <i>d</i>&apos;s of people who are pleased with themselves, and the well closed and rounded <i>o</i>&apos;s of those who are unfathomable, and he replaces his lower-case letters by capitals like hot-headed people who lack all judgement. He belongs to the canaille. He has never been convicted, but his great debts have placed him and his family in the blackest misery. He lives on loans, lies, and he is thirty-five.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 288</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
